Environment limitations:
- Headless Chromium did not complete initialization because the container blocked inotify/NETLINK and lacked DBus.
- The container could not resolve public DNS, so an actual Overpass response could not be proven here.
- Deterministic network fixtures cover success, CORS-style fetch failure, GET fallback, endpoint rotation, persisted preference, timeout/abort diagnostics, parser failure after response and successful graph integration.

Save compatibility:
- Save key unchanged.
- Schema version unchanged.
- New survey diagnostic fields are optional and normalized in place.
- Construction ranges are derived from civilization level and require no migration.
